ABC \equiv 0 \pmod 4
ABC \not\equiv 0 \pmod 4
(2/4)^3 = 1/8
3 \cdot (1/4) \cdot (2/4)^2 = 3/16
P(ABC \not\equiv 0 \mod 4) = 1/8 + 3/16 = 5/16
P(ABC \equiv 0 \mod 4) = 1-P(ABC \not\equiv 0 \mod 4) = 11/16
\frac{44}{4^3}=\frac{11}{16}
